  <brief_title>Thoracic Injuries in Pediatric Polytraumatized Patients: Epidemiology, Treatment and Outcome</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Medical University of Vienna</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Medical University of Vienna</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The present study predicts that concomitant chest injuries in polytraumatized pediatric
      patients are a potential source of substantial morbidity and mortality.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
