        All pediatric (age &lt; 18 years) polytrauma patients with associated thoracic injuries,
        admitted to this Level I Trauma center, between January 1992 and December 2008
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Children with isolated, but severe and potentially life-threatening injuries ISS â‰¥16
        injuries to only one body cavity together with a single long bone fracture thoracic
        injuries

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Injury Severity Score (ISS) of &lt; 16 age &gt;18 no thoracic injuries
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
    <minimum_age>N/A</minimum_age>
    <maximum_age>18 Years</maximum_age>
    <healthy_volunteers>No</healthy_volunteers>
